'''帕特里克·贝尔福，第三代金洛斯男爵'''（{{lang-en|Patrick Balfour, 3rd Baron Kinross}}，{{bd|1904年||1976年|6月4日}}）是一位[[苏格兰|苏格兰]][[历史学家|历史学家]]、[[作家|作家]]，主要作品有[[穆斯塔法·凯末尔·阿塔图尔克|穆斯塔法·凯末尔·阿塔图尔克]]的[[传记|传记]]以及其它和[[伊斯兰世界|伊斯兰世界]]有关的历史书籍<ref>{{cite web |url=http://familytreemaker.genealogy.com/users/d/a/l/Gavin-R-Dallmeyer/WEBSITE-0001/UHP-0103.html |title=Ancestors of Gavin R.J. Dallmeyer: Patrick Balfour |publisher=Familytreemaker.genealogy.com |date=1904-06-25 |accessdate=2013-07-20 |archive-date=2015-02-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150216181717/http://familytreemaker.genealogy.com/users/d/a/l/Gavin-R-Dallmeyer/WEBSITE-0001/UHP-0103.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cracroftspeerage.co.uk/online/content/index1026.htm |title=Cracroft's Peerage |publisher=Cracroftspeerage.co.uk |accessdate=2013-07-20 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/69vukRtZn?url=http://www.cracroftspeerage.co.uk/online/content/index1026.htm |archivedate=2012-08-15 }}</ref>。

==生平==
帕特里克·贝尔福早年就读于[[温切斯特公学|温切斯特公学]]，后进入[[牛津大学贝利奥尔学院|牛津大学贝利奥尔学院]]<ref>Winchester College Register 1915-1960 pp 77-78.</ref>，毕业后成为了一位[[记者|记者]]与作家。

==代表作==
*''The Ruthless Innocent'' (1949) Supposedly based on the character of Angela Culme-Seymour
*''The Orphaned Realm: Journeys in Cyprus'' (1951)
*''Within the Taurus: A Journey in Asiatic Turkey'' (1954)
*《希腊肖像》''Portrait of Greece with photographs in colour by Dimitri, Max Parrish: London (1956)
*''Europa Minor: Journeys in Coastal Turkey'' (1956)
*''The innocents at home'' (1959)
*''Atatürk: The Rebirth of a Nation'' (London. 1964)
*''Atatürk: A Biography of Mustafa Kemal, Father of Modern Turkey'' (New York. 1965)
*《埃及肖像》''Portrait of Egypt'' (1966)
*''Windsor Years: The Life of Edward, as Prince of Wales, King, and Duke of Windsor'' (1967)
*《两海之间：苏伊士运河的建造》''Between Two Seas: The Creation of the Suez Canal'' (1968)
*《奥斯曼帝国六百年》''Ottoman Centuries: The Rise and Fall of the Turkish Empire'' (1977) {{ISBN|0-688-08093-6}}
*《圣索菲亚大教堂：一部君士坦丁堡的历史》''Hagia Sophia :A History of Constantinople'' {{ISBN|9780882250151}} (1979) Newsweek Book Division

